en_845986_0	Mass Media and Finance Minister Mangala Samaraweera has pointed out that the present Government has removed many obstacles to the media.
en_845986_1	Minister Mangala Samaraweera made this reference addressing the 17th Asia Broadcasting Telecommunication Network conference.
en_845986_2	The meeting opened in Colombo under the patronage of Ministers Mangala Samaraweera and John Amaratunge, Deputy Minister Lasantha Alagiyawanna and many local and foreign invitees.
en_845986_3	The aim of establishing the Asia-Pacific Broadcast Development Institute was to create a developed and strong electronic media environment in the area through policies and resource development.
en_845986_4	In his address Minister Mangala Samaraweera said that wide media freedom prevails in Sri Lanka at present.
en_845986_5	He pointed out the significance of holding such meetings to build a new media culture.
en_845986_6	The Minister further pointed out that a new trend of young groups joining the media sphere with the expansion of the social media was being witnessed.
en_845986_7	Expressing his views on the occasion Minister John Amaratunge mentioned the importance of holding such conferences in Sri Lanka to display to the world that Sri Lanka is a safe tourist destination.
